# Kognitos App Builder — Workflow

You are building a domain-specific dashboard app on top of the Kognitos automation platform.
Follow the six phases below **in strict order**. Do NOT skip ahead. Do NOT start coding the app until Phase 6.

## Tech Stack (non-negotiable)

- **Language:** TypeScript only. All code — scripts, helpers, app — must be `.ts` or `.tsx`. No Python scripts.
- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router) deployed to Vercel.
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (or Lattice UI tokens mapped to Tailwind).
- **Chat:** Claude (Anthropic SDK) + Supabase for persistence + Kognitos API tools. See `06-chat-support.mdc`.
- **Arrow IPC decoding:** Use the `apache-arrow` npm package in TypeScript. Never use Python/pyarrow.
- **Runtime:** Node.js with `tsx` for utility scripts in Phases 1-3.

## Phase Sequence

| Phase | Goal | Gate |
|-------|------|------|
| 1 — Environment Setup | API credentials in `.env`, `lib/kognitos.ts` helper, verify connectivity | User picks an automation from the returned list |
| 2 — Discover Automation | Understand chosen automation in plain language, map domain terms | User confirms summary matches their understanding |
| 3 — Inspect Run Outputs | Document data schemas from completed runs | User confirms output schemas are correct |
| 4 — Domain Thinking | Determine useful insights based on actual data | User approves the insight plan |
| 5 — Build Plan | Complete, concrete plan of pages, data flow, and edge cases | User says "build" |
| 5B — Design System | Choose Lattice UI or alternative; configure tokens/layouts/icons | User confirms design system choice |
| 6 — Build the App | Implement the Phase 5 plan using the Phase 5B design system | Working app delivered |

## Gate Rules

- Each phase ends with a clear deliverable and explicit user confirmation.
- **Never assume approval.** Wait for the user to confirm before proceeding.
- Small utility scripts in Phases 1-3 are allowed; the **app itself** starts only in Phase 6.

## Universal Rules

- Never expose API tokens to client-side code.
- Use domain language, not Kognitos jargon, in all user-facing text.
- If unsure about something, ask the user — don't guess at domain meaning.
- At the start of each phase, announce which phase you're entering and what it involves.
- If API calls fail, diagnose before moving on: show the error, suggest fixes, retry.
- Every chart or visualization must answer a specific question from Phase 4.
